<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="E2" checkit-title="Reduced row echelon form">
  <statement>
    <ol>
        <li>Show that <me>\mathrm{RREF}\,\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-3 &amp; -1 &amp; 7 &amp; 4 \\
-3 &amp; -5 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 \\
4 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right].</me></li>
        <li>Explain why the matrix <m>B=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 &amp; 4 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</m> is or is not in reduced row echelon form.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
        <li><me>\mathrm{RREF}\,\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-3 &amp; -1 &amp; 7 &amp; 4 \\
-3 &amp; -5 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 \\
4 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right].</me></li>
        <li>
            <m>B</m> is
                not in reduced row echelon form because
                        the pivots are not descending to the right.
        </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
